Following Tuesdayâ€™s matches in the Champions League, at least six teams are through to the quarter-final stage. Atletico Madrid and Benfica are the latest clubs to seal their spots in the last eight. The Spanish side beat Manchester United 1-0 at Old Trafford to progress with a 2-1 aggregate win. Benfica also saw off Ajax 1-0 in their tie to win it 3-2 on aggregate. The other clubs who will be in the draw for the quarter-finals are Real Madrid, Bayern Munich, Manchester City and Liverpool. The final two will be decided on Wednesday when Chelsea travel to Lille and Juventus take on Villarreal.